      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Knoevenagel condensation is a reaction involving an active methylene compound (a CH<sub>2</sub> flanked by two electron-withdrawing groups) and an aldehyde and ketone. Propose a mechanism for the reaction below.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBcm9ZIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--5effece10ad6c634217ca7a467bafd2f0d74ab2b/OChem_23_EC_019.jpg\" alt=\"The Knoevenagel condensation of diethyl malonate and benzaldehyde with sodium ethoxide forms a conjugated enone. The product shows benzene ring with methine double-bonded to the methylene group of diethyl malonate.\">",
